{"article_id":"T86Hd7mzIHhx59No","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"President Trump on Thursday announced new guidelines","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"for reopening states as soon as May 1","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"now that the coronavirus appears to be peaking in the US ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"but he left the decision up to each state ' s governor","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"while recommending criteria","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that would have to be met","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"for each to gradually reopen .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"\" America wants to be open ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"and Americans want to be open , \"","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Trump said at the White House during the daily Coronavirus Task Force press briefing .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"\" Based on the latest data ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"our team of experts agree","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"we can start the next front in our war ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"which we are calling Opening Up America Again ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and that is what we are doing ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"opening up our country ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"and we have to do that . \"","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Trump stressed","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"that getting the economy back in gear soon would help America recover from the pandemic .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"\" As I have said for some time now ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"a national shutdown is not a sustainable long-term solution .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"To preserve the health of our citizens ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"we must also preserve the health and functioning of our economy .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Over the long haul , you can not do one without the other , \"","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"The president said","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"the task force ' s new guidelines \" will allow governors to take a phased and deliberate approach","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to reopening their individual states , \"","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"but that it would be up to individual governors to make the decisions .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"\" Governors will be empowered to tailor an approach","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that needs the diverse circumstances of their own states .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Every state is very different .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"If they need to remain closed ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"we will allow them to do that ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"if they believe","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"it is time","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"to reopen ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"we will provide them the freedom and guidance","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"to accomplish that task and very , very quickly , \"","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"The Opening Up America Again guidelines say","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"states","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that show a downward trend in COVID-19 cases","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"will be able to reopen restaurants , bars , theaters , workplaces , sporting centers and gyms as soon as May 1 .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"\" Bottom line ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"if you ' re ready","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"and you have those beautiful low numbers","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"like some of you have ,","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"let ' s get going ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"let ' s open up your state , \"","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"Trump told state leaders in a call","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"in which he praised governors for their hard work .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"\" You ' re gon na call your shots . \"","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Under the guidelines , states will need to demonstrate a downward trajectory of COVID-19 cases over a 14-day period and a \" robust \" system","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"for testing health care workers","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"before they can proceed to a phased opening .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Related Video","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"Video length 1 minute 11 seconds 1:11","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"Trump says","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"coronavirus pandemic has peaked ,","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"some states will reopen before May 1","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"Trump says","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"coronavirus pandemic has peaked ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"some states will reopen before May 1","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"The phases ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"as described by task force member Dr. Deborah Birx ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"include :","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Phase 1 ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"which recommends continued social distancing , closure of schools , teleworking and sheltering in place for vulnerable individuals .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"Non-essential travel would be discouraged ,","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"bars should remain closed","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"and visits to nursing homes and hospitals should remain prohibited ,","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"the guidelines warn .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"\" If a vulnerable population needs to return to work ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"there should be special accommodations for all vulnerable populations .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"If the schools are already closed ,","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"they should remain closed , \"","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"Birx said .","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"\" All visits to senior living facilities should continue to be prohibited .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"Large venues can only be operated under strict physical distancing protocols .","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"Gyms could open","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"if they adhere to strict physical distancing . \"","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"Phase 2 allows schools , restaurants and bars to reopen with diminished occupancy .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Non-essential travel can resume ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"and people can gather in groups no larger than 50 ,","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"but teleworking is still encouraged .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"\" This is for the employers .","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"We still would like to encourage telework ,","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"and the common areas should remain closed","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"or be physically distant , \"","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"Birx said .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"\" This should be a relief to many households","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"that have small children :","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"schools , day cares and camps can reopen in Phase 2 .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"Visits to senior living facilities however should remain","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"and hospitals prohibited . \"","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"Phase 3 allows workplaces to reopen with no restrictions ,","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"and visits to senior care centers and hospitals can resume .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"\" It is essentially returning to our new normal .","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"With all of the what we talked about through all phases :","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"continuing the good hygiene practices ,","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"continuing the respect for spaces between individuals ,","depth":17},{"id":104,"text":"because we know","depth":18},{"id":105,"text":"that we still have an issue with asymptomatic spread , \"","depth":18},{"id":106,"text":"she said .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Dr. Anthony Fauci , another expert on the task force , left open the possibility","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"that there could be professional sporting events","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"- with fans in the stands -","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"in Phase 3 of the plan ,","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"which would be around July or August .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"\" The answer is , it is conceivable that we will be able to do that , \"","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"\" I think","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"there will always have to be attention","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"to making sure","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"that we don ' t do all that packing in together .","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"I think","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"we ' ll be able to have sports events in that phase","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"where you actually have participants there . \"","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"\" We ' re going to be back to enjoying sports the way","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"it ' s supposed to be , \"","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"Trump said .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Asked by The Post","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"if states","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"that already meet the preliminary criteria , such as Montana and Utah ,","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"could reopen immediately ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"Trump confirmed","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"that they would .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"\" Yes , they will be able to go literally tomorrow .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Yes ,","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"because the guidelines","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"if you go back ,","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"they ' ve met those guidelines , actually pretty long ago , \"","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"Under the headline \" Core state preparedness responsibilities , \" the federal government ' s plan is asking states to be responsible for testing and screening and securing an independent supply of personal protective equipment .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Earlier Thursday , concerned governors had cautioned Trump against reopening too quickly ,","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"telling him","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"they were still experiencing critical coronavirus test shortages .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"During the conference call","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"in which Trump presented his guidelines","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"to reopen the economy ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"multiple state leaders told him","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"they were still struggling to secure enough complete testing kits","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"and were worried about a second spike in infection .","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"\" We have an enormous lack of manufacturing capability","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"for testing kits themselves , \"","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"said Washington Gov . Jay Inslee ,","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"according to a person familiar with the call .","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"Describing it as a \" hand-to-mouth existence , \"","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"the Democrat said","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"he had more than 160 nursing homes with COVID-19 cases","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"that he could not test","depth":15},{"id":154,"text":"because the state lacked kits and swabs","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"to get the samples","depth":17},{"id":156,"text":"needed for them .","depth":17},{"id":157,"text":"\" That is an extreme limitation ,","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"and we literally are unpacking bags from China by the minute","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"and getting them to a nursing home , \"","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Trump promised to ramp up manufacturing of these testing elements ,","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"5.1 million more swabs would be delivered to states by the end of the month .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"The guidelines were developed by Birx and Fauci in coordination with Centers for Disease Control and Prevention Director Robert Redfield .","depth":7},{"id":165,"text":"Trump also named a bipartisan group of House and Senate members","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"to serve on the Opening Up America Again Congressional Group ,","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"including two New York Republicans , upstate Rep. Elise Stefanik and Long Island Rep. Lee Zeldin .","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"Trump ' s announcement came","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"as seven Northeastern states on Thursday extended their shutdown until May 15","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"to contain the coronavirus pandemic .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":341,"left":0,"right":340,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":340,"left":227,"right":339,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":177,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":174,"right":176,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":173,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":1,"right":172,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":5,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":194,"right":225,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":186,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":179,"right":185,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":179,"left":178,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":184,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":180,"right":183,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":180,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":183,"left":181,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":187,"right":192,"relation":"elabo